\section1 QString

If you specify a negative value for \e len to left() or right() then an empty string is
returned.

\section1 QByteArray

QByteArray is now implicitly shared. It provides most of the
functionality QCString used to provide and is favored over QCString.

* at() now returns a copy and not a reference. If you use at() as an
lvalue use the [] operator instead

* sort() and bsearch() have been removed

* contains(...) returns a bool and not an integer. If you want to count
  the number of occurences of a substring use count(...) instead.

* copy() is obsolete, use regular assignment instead.

\section1 QCString

QCString is deprecated. QByteArray should do everything you need of an
8bit string class. For text handling use QString instead.

The class is now implicitly shared.

Removed methods:

* All methods involving QRegExp as argument have been removed. Use
QString instead if you need to operate with regular expressions on a
string.

changed methods:

* at() now returns a copy and not a reference. If you use at() as an
lvalue use the [] operator instead

\section1 QStringList

QStringList now inherits from QList<QString> and cannot be converted to
a QValueList<QString> anymore. Since QValueList inherits QList a
cast will work as expected.

This change implies some API incompatibilities for QStringList:

* at() returns the string, not an iterator

\section1 QValueList

QValueList now inherits from QList, but is kept source compatible to
the Qt3 class.

\section1 QObject

children() and QueryList now return a QObjectList instead of a pointer
to a QObjectList. See also the comments on QObjectList.

killTimers() has been removed.

\section1 QObjectList

QObjectList is a typdef to a QList of QObject pointers and not a QPtrList now.

\section 1 QPointArray

QPointArray is now implicitly shared and based on QVector.
The return type for the setPoints() and putPoints() functions is now void instead of bool.
isNull() is obsolete, use isEmpty() instead.
copy() is obsolete, use standard assignment instead.

\section1 QWidgetIntDict

Has been removed.

\section1 QWidgetList

QWidgetList is a typdef to a QList of QWidget pointers and not a QPtrList now.

\section1 QApplication

allWidgets() and topLevelWidgets() return a QWidgetList and not a
pointer to a QWidgetList now. This resolves some memory management
issues using these methods.







